Copyright- the exclusive legal right, given to the creator of an original idea that has beem printed, posted, published and preformed.

Copyleft- an arrangement whereby software or art work is used, modified, and/or distributed freely on condition.

Fair use- A US copyright law that allows brief excerpts of copyright material be quoted verbatim for purposes such as criticism, news and reporting.

Free Speech- Freedom of expression and freedom to express thoughts

Free Software- Programs that are free of charge

Freeware- Software that can be freely edited or changed

Public Domain- State of belonging or being available to public

File-Sharing- the practice of or ability to transmit files from one computer to another

Piracy- The unauthorized use or reproduction of other people's work

Plagiarism- Taking credit for someone elses work or ideas

